prvtSaaMib.name: prvtSaaMib

revisions.description: Add CountAllPriorities leaf to SAA Throughput tests.
Add ethertype leaf to SAA Throughput tests.
Add delays to SAA Throughput tests.
Add name leaf to profile table.
Add measurement units for prvtSaaY1731TestResultCompletionTime, fix range for prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapValue.
Add decription for percentile values for jitter and delay in case of outside 1-100 range.
Fix prvtSaaY1731PmTestMonitorInterval range and default value.
Add prvtSaaY1731PmTestProfile description if retued value is 0.
Add detailed description and measurement units on some test result leafs.

prvtSaaMib.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtSaaMib.description: This MIB provides the extended capability of controlling and provisioning various OAM tests and SAA monitoring. It adds extra functionality for DISMAN-PING-MIB

prvtSaaY1731PmTestTable.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestTable
prvtSaaY1731PmTestTable.description: This table holds the configuration for a SAA Y1731 test

prvtSaaY1731PmTestOwner.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestOwner
prvtSaaY1731PmTestOwner.description: This string is used to describe the owner of the Y1731 Pm SAA test.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestName.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestName
prvtSaaY1731PmTestName.description: This string is used to describe the test name for the Y1731 Pm SAA test. It is also used as a test identifier.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestExecStatus.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestExecStatus
prvtSaaY1731PmTestExecStatus.description: SAA Y1731 Pm test execution status.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapType.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapType
prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapType.description: SAA Y1731 Pm test encapsulation type. It can be either test over VLAN or test over Service. The value 1 is the default value representing that neither type is set.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapValue.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapValue
prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapValue.description: The value of the defined SAA Y1731 Pm test encapsulation. It should be either the Vlan ID or the Service ID, depending on the type set in prvtSaaY1731PmTestEncapType.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestUserPort.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestUserPort
prvtSaaY1731PmTestUserPort.description: For SAA Y1731 Pm test, this leaf is used only in case the encapsulation is VLAN type and it determines the port on which the user is connected.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestUplinkPort.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestUplinkPort
prvtSaaY1731PmTestUplinkPort.description: For SAA Y1731 Pm test, this leaf is used only in case the encapsulation is VLAN type and it determines the port that the SAA test devices are connected through.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestTargetMac.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestTargetMac
prvtSaaY1731PmTestTargetMac.description: The target MAC address for the SAA Y1731 test.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestCfmDomainLevel.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestCfmDomainLevel
prvtSaaY1731PmTestCfmDomainLevel.description: CFM Domain level on which the test will be run.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestRemoteCfmMep.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestRemoteCfmMep
prvtSaaY1731PmTestRemoteCfmMep.description: The remote MEP associated with target MAC.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestProfile.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestProfile
prvtSaaY1731PmTestProfile.description: The profile ID associated to the SAA Y1731 Pm test. A value of 0 depicts no set profile.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestPeriod.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestPeriod
prvtSaaY1731PmTestPeriod.description: The period the SAA Y1731 Pm test will run, in milliseconds.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestTimeout.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestTimeout
prvtSaaY1731PmTestTimeout.description: The timeout period for a test packet.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestMonitorInterval.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestMonitorInterval
prvtSaaY1731PmTestMonitorInterval.description: Monitoring interval is relevant only for continous Y1731 test. It is measured in minutes.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestFrequency.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestFrequency
prvtSaaY1731PmTestFrequency.description: The time between two consecutive intervals. A value of 1 defines a delay of a second between the end of the first and the begining of the next interval.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestClocksInSync.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestClocksInSync
prvtSaaY1731PmTestClocksInSync.description: This variable tells if the clocks of the test are syncronized.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayMethod.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayMethod
prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayMethod.description: Defines the method of calculating delay on a Y1731 test.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayPvalue.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayPvalue
prvtSaaY1731PmTestDelayPvalue.description: Percent used to calculate delay in p-percentile method. Reported delay is the percent-th member in the array with sorted delays. Relevant only for p-percentile method. Value in range of 1-100 is for percentile delay method of calculation. Value 101 describes that average delay method of calculation is used. Only values inside the 1..100 range can be set to this parameter.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterMethod.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterMethod
prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterMethod.description: Defines the method of calculating jitter on a Y1731 test.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterPvalue.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterPvalue
prvtSaaY1731PmTestJitterPvalue.description: Percent used to calculate jitter in p-percentile method. Reported jitter is the percent-th member in the array with sorted jitters. Relevant only for p-percentile method. Value in range of 1..100 is for percentile jitter method of calculation. Value 101 describes that peakToPeak jitter method of calculation is used. Value 102 describes that variance jitter method of calculation is used. Only values inside the 1..100 range can be set to this parameter.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestPriority.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestPriority
prvtSaaY1731PmTestPriority.description: Defines the priority of the packets sent by the SAA Y1731 Pm test (priority to count user traffic).

prvtSaaY1731PmTestRowStatus.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestRowStatus
prvtSaaY1731PmTestRowStatus.description: The status of the row. The writable columns in a row can not be changed if the row is active. Certain columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestCCMAPSCount.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestCCMAPSCount
prvtSaaY1731PmTestCCMAPSCount.description: Determines whether to include proactive OAM frames for ETH-CC and ETH-APS in loss measurement counters or not.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestLossMeasurementType.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestLossMeasurementType
prvtSaaY1731PmTestLossMeasurementType.description: If set to 1 Synthetic Loss Measurement will be used for frame-loss calculations.If set 0 user packets will be used for frame-loss calculations

prvtSaaY1731PmTestSLMTransmit.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestSLMTransmit
prvtSaaY1731PmTestSLMTransmit.description: If set true the device is capable of sending SLM packets and frame-loss calculations. This must be used only when loss measurement type is SLM

prvtSaaY1731PmTestTestId.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestTestId
prvtSaaY1731PmTestTestId.description: Specify the unique test id used in Y1731 SLM. 0 means not set.It is mandatory for the Y1731 SLM test

prvtSaaY1731PmTestDropEligible.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestDropEligible
prvtSaaY1731PmTestDropEligible.description: Drop Eligible flag for S-VLAN used for the Y1731 SLM test.

prvtSaaY1731PmTestDataSize.name: prvtSaaY1731PmTestDataSize
prvtSaaY1731PmTestDataSize.description: Packet sizes for Y1731 SLM test

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTable.description: This table holds the configuration for a SAA RFC2544 test

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestOwner.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestOwner
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestOwner.description: This string is used to describe the owner of the RFC2544 SAA test.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestName.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestName
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestName.description: This string is used to describe the test name for the RFC2544 SAA test. It is also used as a test identifier.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestExecStatus.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestExecStatus
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestExecStatus.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput test execution status.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSourceType.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSourceType
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSourceType.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput test source type.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSource.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSource
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestSource.description: String that holds either the MAC or the MEP ID. MAC should be in the format AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF MEP shold be in the format DOMAIN:MA:MEP that represent the values corresponding to dot1agCfmMdIndex, dot1agCfmMaIndex and dot1agCfmMepIdentifier from IEEE8021-CFM-MIB. e.g.: MAC: 00:A0:12:5C:12:C0 MEP: 1:1:2

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTargetType.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTargetType
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTargetType.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput test target type.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTarget.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTarget
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTarget.description: String that holds either the MAC or the MEP ID. MAC should be in the format AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF MEP shold be in the format DOMAIN:MA:MEP that represent the values corresponding to dot1agCfmMdIndex, dot1agCfmMaIndex and dot1agCfmMepIdentifier from IEEE8021-CFM-MIB. e.g.: MAC: 00:A0:12:5C:12:C0 MEP: 1:1:2

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTimeout.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTimeout
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestTimeout.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput test timeout, in 0.1 of a second increments

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCIR.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCIR
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCIR.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput Committed Information Rate (CIR) value.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCBS.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCBS
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCBS.description: SAA RFC2544 Throughput Committed Burst Size (CBS) value.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestBurstPercent.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestBurstPercentage
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestBurstPercent.description: Part of CIR to use for bursts(CBS).

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestDuration.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestDuration
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestDuration.description: The SAA RFC2544 Throughput test duration, in seconds.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestMaxFrameloss.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestMaxFrameloss
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestMaxFrameloss.description: The maximum frameloss to declare a successful SAA RFC2544 Throughput test in 0.001 of a percent.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestCVLAN0.description: C-VLAN ID for the SAA RFC2544 Throughput test.

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestACKTimeout.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestACKTimeout

prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestRowStatus.name: prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestRowStatus
prvtSaaRFC2544ThroughputTestRowStatus.description: The status of the row entry. The writable columns in a row can not be changed if the row is active. Certain columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestEncapType.description: SAA Y1731 Loopback test encapsulation type. It can be either test over VLAN or test over Service. The value 1 is the default value representing that neither type is set.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestEncapValue.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestEncapValue
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestEncapValue.description: The value of the defined SAA Y1731 Lopback test encapsulation. It should be either the Vlan ID or the Service ID, depending on the type set in prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestEncapType.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUserPort.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUserPort
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUserPort.description: For SAA Y1731 Loopback test, this leaf is used only in case the encapsulation is VLAN type and it determines the port on which the user is connected.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUplinkPort.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUplinkPort
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestUplinkPort.description: For SAA Y1731 Loopback test, this leaf is used only in case the encapsulation is VLAN type and it determines the port that the SAA test devices are connected through.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestType.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestType
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestType.description: SAA Y1731 Loopback test type. Specifies the test being perfoer

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestRowStatus.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestRowStatus
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestRowStatus.description: The status of the row entry. The writable columns in a row can not be changed if the row is active. Certain columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestCCMAPSCount.name: prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestCCMAPSCount
prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestCCMAPSCount.description: Determines whether to include proactive OAM frames for ETH-CC and ETH-APS in loss measurement counters or not.

prvtSaaY1731LoopbackTestCountAllPrioriti.description: Determines whether to count all packets ignoring the priority.
